      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Switching to a diet-only approach without medical supervision while taking high-dose garlic and kale juice is extremely dangerous because it can cause erratic clotting, potentially leading to a severe hemorrhage or unintended blood clots. Warfarin is uniquely effective at maintaining stable INR levels precisely because diet fluctuations are monitored, whereas mixing it with massive amounts of garlic destroys this balance in unpredictable ways. You must not attempt to replace medication with supplements alone; instead, consult your doctor about specific alternatives like apixaban or rivaroxaban that may require less frequent or no blood tests depending on your region and health profile. Your safety is too important to risk with unverified natural remedies.",
